From user:

{quote}
 I am now trying to upload a patch for review.

The steps I am taking are as follows:
1. create new review;
2. select "manage files" and "patch" tab;
3. Choose file and select the patch (from file system) as default UTF-8; ...
4. Select "Upload".

Nothing actually happens! Have I missed something in the steps?

Also, is it possible to reference the patch directly in the Jira rather than saving to a file system then trying to upload?

{quote}

If you attempt to send a test email in Bamboo's Administration panel, you'll get this error:

{code}
The mail settings you entered were not valid. Error thrown was: Failed to decrypt.
{code}

The password in {{/data/jirastudio/bamboo/home/bamboo-mail.cfg.xml}} should be using the hashed password, not the plaintext one.

The Studio image will likely need to be fixed.

